<h1>Instructors</h1>

<h2>Simon Apen-Sadler</h2>
{% image "instructors/image.jpg", "Simon Apen-Sadler performing rising block", "instructor-simon" %}
<p>
Simon Apen-Sadler is the Chief Instructor of Northstowe Karate Club. He has over 20 years experience in Shotokan Karate and started training at 8 years old. He is currently a 4th Dan Black Belt with the <a href="https://jka.or.jp/en">JKA</a>. He continues to train regularly at <a href="https://cambridgekaratedojo.com">Cambridge Karate Club</a> with Sensei Ken Hori.
</p>
<p>
  In April 2024, he travelled to Tokyo and Okinawa, to train with some of JKA's top instructors as well as traditional Okinawan karate masters.
</p>
<p>
  He previously trained under Jim Lewis with the KWF and the SKA under Greg Durant.
</p>

